Today, Iraq struck back by rounding up hundreds of foreign nationals in Kuwait as the  U.N. Security Council overwhelmingly approved sweeping trade and military sanctions  to punish it for invading Kuwait.
The U.N. vote was 13 to 0 on the 15-member council.
Cuba and Yemen sustained.
World oil prices soared to their highest level in more than  four years.
While last year's oil revenues totaled more than $11 billion, Iraq has been  pressing for higher oil prices in order to rebuild its war-torn economy and settle foreign  debts of approximately $80 billion.
Warning Iraq, President Bush says all U.S. options  are open. 
